{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3FW04GRAGVJNWWD835XWC","from":"s_01KGY3DZZQG526PJBXPW68F6S7","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"Fact is the tagged union that goes into JSONL. Discriminator is \"t\":\"span\" or \"t\":\"edge\" via serde tag attribute. Every line in a .jsonl file is one Fact.","tags":["type-system","invariant","serialization"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:47:04.836195Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3FW09772YKDK5QNVQQXTV","from":"s_01KGY3E4V25EX3HXQDVK8K1197","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"Span pins a file region. Required: id, path, ns, ts. Optional (skip_serializing_if None): lines [start,end] 1-indexed inclusive, snippet (first line truncated to 80 chars), symbol (semantic anchor), content_hash (12 hex chars of SHA-256), agent, session.","tags":["type-system","invariant"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:47:04.841280Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3FW0R8K5R2SEMKB3H58PT","from":"s_01KGY3E628NAK5X0EPPPG37KQ8","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"Edge links spans or edges. from/to are Option<DamaskId> — both can be null (for notes without a source). rel is a free string classified by vocabulary.rs. payload is arbitrary JSON interpreted via PayloadEnvelope conventions.","tags":["type-system","invariant"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:47:04.856916Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3FWZ6Y1AZN7WTSKETP9C1","from":"s_01KGY3E6KSRFAM5Y3J8T6E057P","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"IDs are \"s_\" or \"e_\" prefix + 26-char ULID = 28 chars total. ULIDs are timestamp-sortable (ms precision). Serde via TryFrom<String>/Into<String> — validated on deserialization. DamaskId discriminates on prefix character.","tags":["type-system","invariant","id"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:47:05.830137Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3FWZAJBCAPBHSJBN5NBEM","from":"s_01KGY3E73P48WV1QXNYDD1WZ6S","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"PayloadEnvelope provides typed access to conventional JSON keys: summary (str), confidence (f64 0-1), status (assertion|hypothesis|ruled_out), evidence (array of str), action (str), tags (array of str). All optional — graceful None on missing keys. Not a schema enforcer, just a convenience accessor.","tags":["type-system","convention","payload"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:47:05.834600Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3FXQJ5WKA163WF9R3HNQ7","from":"s_01KGY3E7NF24SJ15EKT29G3QDX","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"Rel types are classified into 4 tiers: Judgment (risk/gotcha/decision/contradicts/ruled_out/conflicts_with) weight 1.0, Other (custom) weight 0.8, Descriptive (depends_on/supports/describes/derived_from/co_change/implements/env/perf) weight 0.6, Meta (supersedes/invalidates/endorsed/disputed) weight 0.0. Meta edges are structural — they modify other edges, never shown in damask-at output.","tags":["vocabulary","classification","ranking"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:47:06.610563Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3G1RJF92B4NBZAAJ4W8PN","from":"s_01KGY3E88G8WF4GTCFT83NBN18","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"Freshness has two axes: Resolution (Exact=1.0, Relocated=0.7, Unresolved=0.3, Missing=0.0) and Recency (Unchanged, FileChanged, Unknown). A span is fresh if resolution is Exact|Relocated AND recency is Unchanged. Resolution weights feed into ranking signal #1 (currently stubbed). Framework exists but is not yet wired into the query path.","tags":["type-system","freshness","ranking"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:47:10.738421Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3G4XCWWV02GB9D61JKVCE","from":"s_01KGY3EGR25ZSD7SAGB53DBNG1","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"DamaskConfig lives at .damask/config.json. Has default_ns (optional) and per-namespace config (decay_half_life_days, description). Fallback half-life is 90 days. All fields have #[serde(default)] so {} is a valid config.","tags":["configuration","convention"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:47:13.964306Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3GDQNPM4A7KJK8RPXM27Q","from":"s_01KGY3EN6D2ZG18CJB5EG7WFJZ","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.9,"summary":"Error convention: each crate has its own error enum. damask-core::CoreError (InvalidId, Json), damask-resolve::ResolveError (Io, MissingFile), damask-store::StoreError (Io, Json, AlreadyInitialized, NotFound). CLI wraps everything with anyhow::Result and .context() for nested messages. I/O errors are lossy-converted to String via .map_err(|e| StoreError::Io(e.to_string())).","tags":["convention","error-handling"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:47:22.997864Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3GHYRNR46NBMJ24A16Y7B","from":"s_01KGY3EP8GDZ0YQ0A745581XF1","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"DamaskProject manages the .damask/ directory. Discovery walks upward from cwd looking for .damask/ dir. Namespace resolution priority: DAMASK_NS env var > .damask/.active_ns file > --ns CLI flag. Namespaces map 1:1 to JSONL files: .damask/edges/<ns>.jsonl. list_namespaces() derives namespace list from filenames in edges/ dir.","tags":["architecture","project","namespace"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:47:27.320215Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3GQJS9BCBMG0P9SQ2SNPA","from":"s_01KGY3EPZ54X5MX06WMCB41KNS","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"Edge active state is computed in SQLite after index build. 3-step process: (1) All edges start is_active=1, (2) Edges targeted by effective supersedes edges become is_active=0 (a supersedes is effective unless it is itself targeted by an invalidates edge), (3) All meta-rel edges (supersedes/invalidates/endorsed/disputed) become is_active=0 for display. This means invalidating a supersedes reinstates the original edge.","tags":["state-machine","invariant","core-logic"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:47:33.081984Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3GWT57VJN4A3FG55QB8QN","from":"s_01KGY3EQFFMW89HFWF84J0EGTQ","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"Exponential decay: score = 0.5^(age_days / half_life_days). Brand new = 1.0, at half-life = 0.5, at 2x half-life = 0.25. Default half-life 90 days (configurable per-namespace). half_life=0 disables decay (returns 1.0). Effective timestamp uses latest endorsement time if available, otherwise edge creation time — endorsements reset the decay clock.","tags":["ranking","decay","convention"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:47:38.437727Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3HKM8XKV9137R4ZC1M453","from":"s_01KGY3ERCK4ZE6RC91Q9BVGZS9","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.9,"summary":"Predicates are single field-op-value expressions. Operators: = != > < >= <=. Fields: rel, ns, agent (string); confidence (numeric); status, summary (payload envelope); tags (array contains); endorsed, disputed (numeric or bool). No AND/OR compositing in phase 1.","tags":["query","convention","predicate"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:48:01.800737Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3HMWZ1JRBH9N2QANRM3ZV","from":"s_01KGY3ES3F56TGJ8N1FMKCEGMK","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"Content hash is truncated SHA-256: first 6 bytes = 12 hex chars. Computed from span text (lines joined by newline). Used for freshness detection. Hash stored on Span.content_hash (optional).","tags":["resolve","hashing","invariant"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:48:03.103500Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3J0SNED3MYFQMZG4ENJRX","from":"s_01KGY3ET068MB38H73RY2Q8SNQ","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"The flagship query command. Flow: parse file:line -> discover .damask/ -> update_index (full rebuild) -> spans_at(path, line) -> for each span: edges_for_span -> for each edge: get endorsement_count, dispute_count, latest_endorsement_ts -> build RankingInput -> rank_edges(inputs, limit=12) -> display sorted by score. Deduplicates edges seen across multiple overlapping spans.","tags":["data-flow","query","flagship"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:48:15.285963Z"}
{"t":"edge","id":"e_01KGY3J55X7VAHRP92K0H9MQC5","from":"s_01KGY3EVYWZTHSK5ZJ1JZ6HDB4","to":null,"rel":"describes","payload":{"confidence":0.95,"summary":"Span creation flow: validate lines (1-indexed, start <= end) -> discover .damask/ -> resolve namespace (--ns flag or active_ns()) -> read source file -> extract first line as snippet (truncated 80 chars, UTF-8 safe) -> compute content_hash via damask_resolve -> create Span with SpanId::new() -> wrap in Fact::Span -> append to .damask/edges/<ns>.jsonl via FactWriter.","tags":["data-flow","creation"]},"ns":"architecture","ts":"2026-02-08T07:48:19.773860Z"}
